                    <div>
                        <head>State of preservation</head>
                        <p>Very good; the surface is fairly even. Two oblong holes lie within the field of script and result in the loss of characters; one, in segment 2A, 179–180.5 cm above the floor; and the other in segment 9A, 168–171 cm above the floor and 85–91.5 cm from wall c. Some areas within the first 15 columns near the entrance are worn away. A large dark grey area caused by damp spreads over the central portion of the wall. </p>
